				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\oslash$$\end{document}⊘ 0.6 mm pitch) sandwiched between two scintillator sheets (0.25 mm and 0.45 mm thick) and aluminium optical masks with 0.2 mm openings on a 0.6 mm pitch. A 5 mm B4C plate to reduce neutron background is placed behind the second scintillator. Pictures on the right show the detector size and geometry of the final assembly.

